choices.text: You are given two integers A and B. Print a grid where each square is painted white or black that satisfies the following conditions, in the format specified in Output section: - Let the size of the grid be h \times w (h vertical, w horizontal). Both h and w are at most 100. - The set of the squares painted white is divided into exactly A connected components. - The set of the squares painted black is divided into exactly B connected components. It can be proved that there always exist one or more solutions under the conditions specified in Constraints section. If there are multiple solutions, any of them may be printed.
